Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP)
 


overview

Financials
Credit Ratings
Deposit Guarantee
Bank Identifiers



  


















Banco Comercial Portugues was esstablished in 1985. In 2004 
Banco Comercial Portugues was rebranded as Millennium BCP and Banque BCP. 
Banco Comercial Portugues operates as a universal bank, providing a broad 
range of retail, private, corporate and investment banking products and services.In 2015 total assets of Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP)  were 54 151,12 mln EUR.  In 2015 the bank's net income was 226,06 mln EUR.  Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) is rated by Fitch, Moody's. Long-term credit rating assigned to the bank by Fitch is BB-  (speculative). Long-term credit rating assigned to the bank by Moody's is B1  (highly speculative).  Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) participates in deposit guarantee scheme of Portugal. 
This scheme covers accounts up to 100 000 EUR per bank per depositor.  Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) is a member of 
				Millennium BCP (Portugal). Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) is headquartered in Porto.




AddressPç. D. João I, 28, 4000-295, Porto, Portugal 

Head of Group Millennium BCP (Portugal)  
 


