Credit Rating is an opinion of a credit rating agency about credit worthiness of a company 
		or a government. Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) is rated by Fitch and Moody's.
Credit ratings assigned to Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) as of April 2016 are shown in details in the following sections.
FitchLong-term issuer default rating is Fitch's view of a credit institution's relative vulnerability 
		to default on its financial obligations, for Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) it is set to BB-  (speculative), outlook is stable  (not likely to change). The rating is not on watch. Short-term issuer default rating for Banco Comercial Portugues, SA (BCP or Millennium BCP) is set to B  (speculative short-term credit quality).
