Banco Comercial Português SA in Financial Cards and Payments (Portugal)

November 2015
2 pages
Euromonitor International
        

Report ID: 2159360



Summary
Table of contents
Search Inside


		After a period marked by financial instability, Banco Comercial Português, best known by the label Millennium BCP, expects sustained growth over the forecast period. Business strategies are expected to focus on investment in new technologies, mainly directed to digital platforms (mobile and internet banking), and in the adjustment of the business model to more-efficiently attract clients. Small and medium-sized enterprises, together with microenterprises, are anticipated to continue playing...Euromonitor International Local Company Profiles are a concise set of briefings detailing the strategic direction taken by a company. Discover key contact details, the company background and their competitive positioning through this collection of snapshot company profiles.Product coverage: Financial Cards in Circulation, M-Commerce, Transactions. Data coverage: market sizes (historic and forecasts), company shares, brand shares and distribution data.Why buy this report?* Get a detailed picture of the Financial Cards and Payments market;* Pinpoint growth sectors and identify factors driving change;* Understand the competitive environment, the market’s major players and leading brands;* Use five-year forecasts to assess how the market is predicted to develop.


